race.comment: VIKING VALOUR (4) scored at this track last time out by 1.5L over today's journey at a short price. Has an awkward barrier but looks to have turned the corner and can win again with average luck. UNDER SUSPICION (2) has scored at his last two starts, most recently by 1.7L over 1000m at Cloncurry as favourite. Keeps improving, and he can feature again. TEQUILA DANCER (5) is close to a win after a string of minor placings, the latest over 1000m at Home Hill. Carries more weight but can figure prominently again. WITHOUT (10) met with solid support but was plain over 800m at Twin Hills. She flopped prior as well, but the lead-up to that read okay. Placed her only run here at the trip, and we may see more from her today. Something for the Multiples: POLLY HOFFA (9)
